### Multi Map — Feature TODO

- A living document for proposed features, improvements, and design intentions.
- Add items freely. Expand into detail before implementation.
- Items are ordered by dependency and recommended execution sequence.

---

### [ ] Phase 1: The Data & Identity Layer
- Agent Context: firestore.rules, multi-map-core.js (data manager), multi-map-library.js, auth.js, Firebase Admin functions.

### [x] 1. Guest-to-Auth Data Migration
- Intent: Ensure a seamless transition when a user "graduates" from guest mode to an authenticated account without losing work.
- Details:
  - When a user signs in (handled in auth.js via onAuthStateChanged), scan local storage/IndexedDB for existing guest projects.
  - Merge these w/ user’s local projects using the logic inside multi-map-library.js (e.g., expanding loadLocalProjects()).
  - Dynamically update the Data Manager UI to merge and display these newly migrated projects alongside any existing local ones, without requiring a hard refresh.
  - Clear the local guest cache once migration is confirmed successful to prevent duplication.

---

### [x] 2. Federated Storage & Quota Management UI
- Intent: Implement the first stage of the federated architecture. Firebase acts as the central directory and offers limited default storage, while the UI prompts users to "Bring Your Own Storage" (Local OS or Google Drive) to bypass quotas and own their data.
- Specification: feature-specs/prep-federated-spec.md
- Details:
  - Update map schema to include a storage_target property (firebase, google_drive, local_os).
  - Implement a soft and hard storage cap on Firebase-hosted maps (e.g., limit on total map count or node count for free users).
  - Add a capacity warning UI: When a user hits 80% capacity, prompt them with: "Your cloud workspace is almost full. Connect Google Drive or a Local Directory for unlimited free storage."
  - Update the Data Manager UI (multi-map-core.js, multi-map-ui.css) to allow users to select their primary "Vault" (storage location) and visually distinguish the storage target of each project with distinct icons.
  - Ensure Firebase correctly stores lightweight "pointers" (external IDs or local IndexedDB references) rather than full payloads for maps hosted on external targets.

---

### [ ] 3. Map Sharing / Public Links
- Intent: Allow users to share a read-only link to any map in their library.
- Details:
  - Add a shared: boolean flag and a share_token: string field to mapstate-schema.json.
  - "Share" action in the Data Manager generates a unique share_token (UUID), sets shared: true, and writes the map to a public Firestore collection: shared_maps/{share_token}.
  - Update firestore.rules to allow public read access to the shared_maps collection.
  - Public URL format: https://mm.forestneff.com/view/{share_token}.
  - Create a lightweight view.html page that renders the shared map in read-only map mode (stripping out inspector panels and editing event listeners from multi-map-core.js).
  - Shared maps show a "Fork to my workspace" button for authenticated visitors.
  - Revoke sharing: sets shared: false and deletes the shared_maps document.
  - Expiry option: shared links can optionally expire after 7 / 30 / 90 days.

---

### [ ] 4. AI Telemetry & Automated Feedback
- Intent: Capture user friction and bug reports directly via the AI widget to improve agentic workflows and pinpoint engine errors.
- Details:
  - Create a structured feedback and error schema in Firestore. Ensure firestore.rules permits users to write to this log collection.
  - Automate log capture when possible (e.g., "User attempted [Action], got [Error Type], navigated away after [X] seconds"). Tie into the logger.js service.
  - Add a user-facing feature suggestion/bug report form launched directly from the AI widget (multi_map_ai_engine.js). Call automatically if user intent is parsed as "suggestion."
  - Route all captured telemetry and feedback to the admin.html dashboard (populated via functions/routes/admin.js) for developer review.

---

### [ ] Phase 2: The Portal & Agent Paradigm Shift
- Agent Context: phase-engines.js, engines/*, mapstate-schema.json, Portal logic (multi-map-core.js), AI Agent prompt definitions.

---

### [ ] 5. Smart Roots
- Intent: Upgrade root nodes so they contain structured metadata for their maps that they can easily pass to portals that call them or that exist within them.
- Specification: feature-specs/smart-roots-spec.md
- Details:
  - Define a standardized root_metadata object schema specifically for root nodes in mapstate-schema.json.
  - Implement UI in the inspector/properties panel (multi-map-core.js or multi-map-ui.css layouts) for defining and editing this root node metadata.
  - Ensure this metadata payload is bundled and readily accessible when generating or evaluating a portal link.

---

### [ ] 6. Dynamic Portals
- Intent: Deprecate the bespoke "smart portal" and make all portals dynamic, data-driven endpoints that utilize the new Smart Root metadata natively within the host map.
- Specification: feature-specs/dynamic-portals-spec.md
- Details:
  - Portals serve as map endpoints — no generic user map editing past a portal.
  - Implement an openPortal() method to dynamically auto-spawn children and behavior locally in the current host map based on the root node type and explicitly passed metadata payloads from the Smart Root.
  - Preserve the existing enterPortal() method strictly for standard submap page traversal.
  - Remove the manual "add node" button from the portal radial menu (tutorials/radial_menu.json / multi-map-rules.js logic) for these dynamic nodes.
  - Standardize the metadata passing/pulling architecture across the portal boundary, implementing explicit local handoffs of the Smart Root data.

---

### [ ] 7. Flowchart Maptype
- Intent: Introduce a dedicated maptype designed specifically for plotting logic flows, workflow automation, and state machines (useful for the agent-root sub-components, timelines, and project design).
- Specification: feature-specs/flowchart-spec.md
- Details:  
  - Define schema rules for directional relationships (beyond standard parent/child trees) in mapstate-schema.json.
  - Implement custom radial menu and rendering rules for flowchart nodes (e.g., decision diamonds, conditional branches/logic gates) in multi-map-rules.js and the canvas rendering loop.

---

### [ ] 8. Expand Prompt-Root and Agent-Root Ecosystems
- Intent: Utilize the map-native interface to design and build structured, complex, high-quality prompts and agent architectures that can then be exported for use with external LLMs/Agentic Systems (like Antigravity).
- Specification: feature-specs/prompt-root-spec.md & feature-specs/agent-root-spec.md
- Details:
  - Prompt Ecosystem
    - Expand the prompt-root maptype to build/handle structured prompts, complex prompt chaining, variable injection, and prompt-library management. Expand sub-type hierarchy in mapstate-schema.json.
    - Flesh out engines/prompt-engine.html as a dedicated sandbox viewport w/ the ability to export the structured prompt as a .md or raw text (via string builder logic).
  - Agent Ecosystem
    - Expand the agent-root maptype to configure system instructions, tool access, and agentic workflows. Ensure compatibility with templates found in .agents/skills/.
    - Flesh out engines/agent-config.html as a dedicated sandbox viewport that provides a dynamic overview of the agent architecture, including an option to export as a .zip file structure.
    - Allow multi_map_ai_engine.js logic to dictate the dynamic layout of portals linking to these specific roots.

---

### [ ] 9. File-Root Maptype & Local File System Explorer
- Intent: Create a map-native local file-system explorer for seamless local file management within Multi-Map.
- Specification: feature-specs/file-root-spec.md
- Details:
  - Integrate file-root maptypes into mapstate-schema.json.
  - Utilize the browser's HTML5 File System Access API (where supported) to read local directory structures and represent them as dynamic child nodes.
  - Build a corresponding phase engine (engines/file-explorer.html) and register it in phase-engines.js. It should provide a specialized viewport for viewing, organizing, and executing basic file operations.

---

### [ ] 10. Third-Party Cloud Storage Integrations
- Intent: Extend the file system mapping capabilities to interact with external cloud drives.
- Specification: feature-specs/third-party-cloud-spec.md
- Details:
  - Implement authentication and API bridging for services like Google Drive and Google Docs. Expand Firebase Auth providers in auth.js to request Drive OAuth scopes.
  - Enable syncing, fetching, and map-native representation of external cloud files. Ensure OAuth tokens and API limits are handled safely (utilizing functions/middleware/rateLimit.js).

---

### [ ] 11. Launch True Federation (WebRTC + CRDTs)
- Intent: Transition Multi-Map from a centralized Firebase payload host to a true peer-to-peer (P2P) federated network, relegating Firebase strictly to an identity and WebRTC signaling switchboard.
- Specification: feature-specs/launch-federation-spec.md
- Details:
  - Transition the local memory map states (state.nodes) to a CRDT framework (like Yjs or Automerge).
  - Implement WebRTC signaling using Firebase Firestore to exchange connection offers and ICE candidates between peers.
  - NOTE (from TODO #3): The shared_maps Firestore collection currently stores full map payloads per share token.
    When federation ships, replace this with a lightweight pointer (owner_uid + map_id) and serve
    shared maps directly from the peer network. This eliminates duplication and aligns with the CRDT model.
  - Shift the primary network transport for live collaborative map edits from Firestore onSnapshot to direct P2P WebRTC data channels.
  - Ensure data persistence fallbacks utilize the user's primary "Vault" (Drive/Local OS) as defined in previous steps. 

---

### [ ] Phase 3: Core Mechanics & Interaction Stability
- Agent Context: multi-map-core.js, multi-map-rules.js, Keyboard event listeners, functions/index.js.

---

### [ ] 12. Standard Keyboard Editing
- Intent: Implement standard mind-map keyboard shortcuts for rapid, mouse-free node creation and navigation.
- Details:
  - Bind these to the main global keydown event listener in multi-map-core.js.
  - Tab: Trigger existing addChildNode() logic attached to the currently selected node and automatically focus it for text entry.
  - Enter: Trigger existing addSiblingNode() logic at the same hierarchical level as the currently selected node and automatically focus it for text entry.
  - Arrow Keys (Up/Down/Left/Right): Navigate node selection along branches based on spatial and hierarchical relationships.

---

### [ ] 13. Multi-Level Undo / Redo Polish
- Intent: Implement a multi-level undo/redo system that persists across the new dynamic portal navigations.
- Details:
  - Isolate undo/redo state arrays inside the kernel map object (e.g., window.kernel.maps[map_id].history) instead of a global array.
  - On enterPortal, push the current state onto the child map's history; the parent map's history is frozen but preserved. On exitPortal, restore the parent map's history stack.
  - Redo stack: clear the redo stack for a specific map when a new action is taken (e.g., inside saveHistory()).
  - Cap history depth at 50 entries per map to limit memory.
  - Keyboard: Bind Ctrl/Cmd+Z = undo, Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+Z = redo to the global key listener.
  - Show current undo depth as a subtle counter on the undo button (↩️ 3).

---

### [ ] 14. Node Search / Global Jump
- Intent: Extend the existing nav search bar to support cross-map semantic search, natively understanding the new dynamic portal endpoints.
- Details:
  - Tier 1: Initialize Fuse.js in multi-map-library.js for local fuzzy search that filters state.nodes by title/content for instant DOM results.
  - Tier 2: Cross-map search across all library pages, surfacing results with [Page Name] › Node Title breadcrumbs.
  - Selecting a cross-map result opens/creates a portal to that page and fires selectNode() on the matched node.
  - Keyboard shortcut: Cmd/Ctrl + K opens the search bar with focus.
  - AI Semantic Search: Create a new /api/search endpoint in functions/index.js that embeds and vector-searches across log-stored maps.

---

### [ ] Phase 4: Social & Collaborative Expansion
- Agent Context: engines/colab-engine.html, engines/person.html, multi-map-library.js, Realtime Database/Firestore Listeners, firestore.rules.

---

### [ ] 15. Colab-Root, Communities, & Shared Spaces
- Intent: Introduce an entirely new colab-root system that acts as a dedicated container for social networks, communities, and collaborative spaces.
- Specification: feature-specs/contacts-communities-spec.md
- Details:
  - Introduce a new colab-root maptype and a dedicated phase engine (engines/colab-engine.html) to manage organizational structures, shared maps, and user roles.
  - Introduce organizational sub-types: colab-organization, colab-community, and colab-group. Update mapstate-schema.json.
  - Incorporate existing person objects (contacts, user profiles) as sub-types or dynamically reference them via portals inside the colab-root.
  - Connect multiplayer instances securely utilizing the new WebRTC P2P mesh established in Item #11.
  - Update firestore.rules heavily to enforce Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) based on the acl metadata for colab-root nodes to ensure only authorized users can initiate P2P handshakes.

---

### [ ] Phase 5: Platform Delivery & Documentation
- Agent Context: service-worker.js, manifest.json, multi-map-tutorials.js, wiki.html.

---

### [ ] 16. Robust Wiki & Auto-Driven Tutorial System
- Intent: Build a robust, map-native Wiki alongside an automated tutorial system to document the finished architecture.
- Details:
  - Substantially expand wiki.html to act as the central documentation hub, linking directly to map states and tutorials in tutorials/*.json.
  - Refine multi-map-tutorials.js to parse new autoNav and autoSelect fields.
  - Connect autoNav to PhaseEngine.switchView() (from phase-engines.js) and autoSelect to the node selection logic in multi-map-core.js.
  - Implement CSS spotlight overlays (in multi-map-ui.css) to highlight specific DOM elements during tutorial steps.
  - Add step validators in multi-map-tutorials.js: the "Next" button only activates once the user successfully completes the requested UI interaction.
  - Persist tutorial progress to localStorage to survive page refreshes.

---

### [ ] 17. PWA / Offline Mode
- Intent: Package the app as a Progressive Web App so it can be installed natively and continue working on flaky connections.
- Details:
  - Add a Web App Manifest (manifest.json): app name, icons, theme color, display: standalone.
  - Implement a service-worker.js with a cache-first strategy for all static assets (HTML, JS, CSS, phase engines, tutorial/wiki JSON).
  - Tie IndexedDB caching into multi-map-library.js fetch routines so active project maps are readable/editable offline.
  - Sync queue: changes made offline are written to a local queue and flushed to Firestore when connectivity returns (using the Background Sync API).
  - Add an offline indicator in the nav bar and an "Install Multi-Map" prompt after 3 sessions.


### Notes:

1. Allow guest users to share their maps, simply publish them to firestore as anon links. 

2. Change "Save Submap" radial menu button to "Clip". Remains more or less as is but clips the branch from the parent map to a new page and replaces the selected node w/ a portal that points to that page where the cliped branch is preserved, using the original node as the root. *Remove "Clip" button from root and portal radials, do not allow clipping of root, do not allow clipping of nodes that are themselves portals.

3. When a right drawer is open, clicking in viewport (ouside of drawer) should close profile or data drawer (not inspector).

4. Add "Cloud Sync" button to projects and pages (projects that are synced auto-sync all project pages) for projects/pages from non-cloud vaults. When a project or page is marked for cloud sync, add it to the cloud sync vault. Respect user quota. Add an "All Vaults" option to Data Vault dropdown that shows all available projects sorted by category (local, cloud sync, cloud only) - local projects and cloud synced projects shown in local vaults, cloud only projects shown in cloud vaults, same project won't show up in both. Cloud vault should show both local cloud synced and cloud only projects.

5. While we're in the auth stuff, let's address the special case for the production site where I am signed in. Let's add an admin user tier with no quotas/restrictions and special access. To start out with, I need access to the admin.html, so the interface should update to give me a button in my profile drawer that links there. Only admin accounts get this button. How can we set up my Google acount to be an admin account?

6. Extract the rename tool button from the page actions toolbar and place it directly next to the title of the page. Extract download, copy, and share, and delete buttons from that same toolbar into a dropdown w/ a tools icon button to open it. Keep the "load" tool at the top level leftmost as is, place the "tools" button to the right of it. Consider parent card overflow rules so that the dropdown renders correctly (on top as we did w/ the asset import project selection dropdown).

7. Data manager workspace library visible but not populating (empty, doesn't show projects/pages but does allow them to be created) when vault set to cloud. 
